            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "PERES; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thy kingdom is divided — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Or broken from thee. The word PERES signifies ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "broken; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and it also signifies the nation of the Persians, for they were called ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Paros, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "by the Chaldeans: so that this word not only signified that the Babylonish kingdom should be broken, but also by whom it should be broken. UPHARSIN, the other word in the writing, is a participle of the same verb from whence PERES is derived, and literally signifies, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And they divide it. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Concerning Belshazzar’s destruction, see notes on Isaiah 14.",
        "children": []
      },
